Tukur Muntari, Kano A Magistrates’ Court in Kano on Tuesday remanded a 35-year-old carpenter, Balarabe Usaini, in a correctional facility for allegedly defiling a 12-year-old girl. The defendant is facing one count of rape. The prosecutor, Inspector Pogu Lale, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on July 29, 2020, at Unguwa Uku in Kano metropolis. Lale said the girl was sent on an errand by her mother and the defendant lured her into his house and defiled her. According to Lale, the offence contravened section 283 of the penal code. The defendant, however, denied committing the offence. The Chief Magistrate, Muhammad Jibril, ordered that the defendant be remanded at the state correctional facility and the case file be sent to the Directorate of Public Prosecutions for advice. He adjourned the case till September 17, 2020. Meanwhile, two men, Ado Lawan, 43, and Lawan Ibrahim, 34, on Tuesday appeared before a Chief Magistrates’ Court sitting in Kano over alleged adultery. Lale told the court that one Haruna Isa of Rijiyar Lemo Quarters Kano, reported the case at Market Police Division Kano, on August 4, 2020. Copyright PUNCH.
